    <p>Me­gan Thee Stal­lion</p>
    <p>2020 has been a stel­lar year for Amer­i­can rap­per Me­gan Thee Stal­lion (right), with her two col­lab­o­ra­tions – Sav­age (Remix) with Bey­once and WAP with Cardi B – hit­ting No. 1 on the US charts.</p>
    <p>The Grammy-nom­i­nated artist tops it all off with her de­but al­bum, the aptly ti­tled Good News. Her rhyme mas­tery, trade­mark feisti­ness and li­bidi­nous lyrics ap­pear ef­fort­less. Tracks such as Body show off her pen­chant for hooks, while Don’t Rock Me To Sleep sees her step­ping out of her South­ern hip-hop com­fort zone to take on synth-heavy pop.</p>
    <p>As with any mod­ern rap al­bum, there are guest stars aplenty – from DaBaby to SZA – but none threat­ens her dom­i­nance on the 17 tracks.</p>
    <p>Her larger-than-life per­son­al­ity comes to the fore – most ex­cep­tion­ally on Girls In The Hood, in which she puts a fe­male-cen­tric spin on late rap lu­mi­nary Eazy-E’s 1987 brag­gado­cios clas­sic Boyz-n-the-Hood.</p>

